bugtrap03.misc

Class Tree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • bugtrap03.misc.Tree<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>

    public class Tree<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>
    A Tree data structure with an empty root node.
    This collection is based on nodes holding values.
    Removing a value does not result in removing the nodes unless the specific methods (removeTree(java.lang.Object), sizeObjNb()) are used.
    The Iterators included will not ignore these left-over-empty-nodes and will iterate over with null values.
    Author:
    Group 03

      • toArray

        public java.lang.Object[] toArray()
        Returns an array containing all of the elements in this collection.
        If this collection makes any guarantees as to what order its elements are returned by its iterator, this method must return the elements in the same order. The returned array will be "safe" in that no references to it are maintained by this collection. (In other words, this method must allocate a new array even if this collection is backed by an array). The caller is thus free to modify the returned array. This method acts as bridge between array-based and collection-based APIs.
        Specified by:

      • add

        public boolean add(T e)
        Ensures that this collection contains the specified element.
        This will add the element in a new tree node attached to this Tree.
        Caution: null can be added but not removed by remove(java.lang.Object), only by removeTree(java.lang.Object) and clearLeftNull().
        Specified by:

        Parameters:

        Returns true if this collection changed as a result of the call.

      • remove

        public boolean remove(java.lang.Object o)
        Removes a single instance of the specified element from this collection, if it is present (optional operation).
        More formally, removes an element e such that (o==null ? e==null : o.equals(e)), if this collection contains one or more such elements. Returns true if this collection contained the specified element (or equivalently, if this collection changed as a result of the call).

        Clarification: This will remove based on the values held in the tree nodes. When such a value is found the the value is only removed from that node but the node remains. (Check removeTree(java.lang.Object) to remove whole trees).

        When o == null no changes will be made as removing results in setting the value to null.

        Specified by:
        remove in interface java.util.Collection<T>
        Parameters:
        o - - element to be removed from this collection, if present
        Returns:
        True if the element was removed due to this call.

      • clearLeftNull

        public void clearLeftNull()
        Clear the dangling null values.
        Every Tree that does not contain any non null value in the node and below in all its subTrees will be removed.

      • removeTree

        public boolean removeTree(java.lang.Object o)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
